    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Encyclia subulatifolia are its antioxidant activity, which is attributed to the presence of flavonoids such as kaempferol and quercetin. This plant also exhibits anti-inflammatory properties due to the presence of saponins, which are known to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes. The anti-microbial properties of Encyclia subulatifolia are attributed to the volatile oils present in its leaves, including terpinen-4-ol and geraniol, which have been shown to inhibit the growth of various microorganisms. Its anti-diabetic properties are due to the presence of bioactive compounds that stimulate insulin secretion and improve glucose metabolism. Additionally, the plant's leaves contain bioactive compounds that have been shown to exhibit anti-cancer properties by inducing apoptosis and inhibiting cell proliferation.",
