    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Encyclia subulatifolia are derived from its flowers and leaves, which are rich in flavonoids and phenolic acids. A tincture is made by steeping the flowers in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin to create a concentrated liquid extract with potential antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties. Encyclia subulatifolia tea is prepared by infusing the flowers or leaves in hot water, which has been traditionally used to treat respiratory issues such as bronchitis and coughs. An infusion of the plant is also used to create a salve, which may be applied topically to soothe skin irritations and wounds. The essential oil of Encyclia subulatifolia can be extracted through steam distillation and has been reported to possess insecticidal and antimicrobial activities.",
