    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Encyclia subulatifolia improperly are develop skin irritation due to its sap being an irritant and potentially causing dermatitis or contact dermatitis, induce nausea and experience nausea due to its toxic and volatile oils, develop allergic reaction and experience allergic reaction as some individuals may be allergic to its sap or other components, this is because Encyclia subulatifolia contains toxic compounds such as alkaloids and glycosides that can cause adverse reactions, improper use of this plant can lead to these side effects as its toxic compounds can be released when handled or ingested.",
    "uses": "Encyclia subulatifolia is known to have various medicinal properties, but its usage in traditional medicine is limited. It is reported to have antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties, which could contribute to its potential medicinal uses. The plant contains compounds like alkaloids and glycosides, which are known to have medicinal properties. However, further research is needed to fully understand and utilize its medicinal properties effectively. Its medicinal uses are still being studied and require more scientific evidence to support their validity.",
    "taxonomy": "Encyclia subulatifolia is classified as a species within the genus Encyclia, which belongs to the family Orchidaceae. This genus is a group of orchids commonly known as the \"encyclias\". The family Orchidaceae, to which Encyclia subulatifolia belongs, comprises around 32,000 species of orchids. The taxonomy of Encyclia subulatifolia places it within the subtribe Spiranthinae, which is a subunit of the tribe Cranichideae. The classification of Encyclia subulatifolia is subject to ongoing research and potential revisions.",
    "benefits": "Encyclia subulatifolia is known to have potential health benefits due to its bioactive compounds, including flavonoids and phenolic acids, which can exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. These compounds may help protect against cell damage, reduce inflammation, and improve overall health. Additionally, some studies suggest that Encyclia subulatifolia extracts may possess antimicrobial and antifungal properties, which could aid in wound healing and infection prevention. Further research is necessary to fully understand the health benefits of Encyclia subulatifolia, but its unique compounds show promise for various applications. More studies are required to confirm the efficacy and safety of Encyclia subulatifolia for human consumption.",
    "parts": "Encyclia subulatifolia is a species of orchid, and there is limited information available about its medicinal properties. However, in some traditional medicinal practices, the flowers and leaves of this plant are used to treat various health issues. The flowers are said to have anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. The leaves are used to treat fever and other respiratory problems. More research is needed to confirm the effectiveness of these medicinal properties.",
    "intro": "Encyclia subulatifolia, also known as the needle-leaved Encyclia, is a species of orchid native to the tropical forests of Central and South America. This plant has been traditionally used in folk medicine for its potential health benefits, including anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, which may aid in the treatment of various ailments such as wounds, fever, and respiratory issues. The bioactive constituents of Encyclia subulatifolia include flavonoids, alkaloids, and saponins, which have been shown to exhibit antioxidant and immunomodulatory activities. In traditional herbal medicine, Encyclia subulatifolia is often prepared as a decoction, infusion, or tincture, and is used to treat a range of conditions, including skin problems, digestive issues, and respiratory infections."
